# 6. ライブ後は打ち上げで

Shindo: Nice work, everyone.
Shindo: What did you think of your first big festival?
Saki: It was so much fun!!
Ichika: It was...!
Honami: And we all performed so well...!
Shiho: We were actually a little worried at first since not many people had gathered.
Shindo: That isn't your fault, since you're still trying to get your name out there. After all, you debuted only just recently.
Shindo: However, in terms of raising your name recognition, Leo/need absolutely succeeded in that department today.
Saki: Yeah, we did...!
Saki: But the crowd felt so far away from the stage. That bothered me a little, since I couldn't really see everyone's faces...
Saki: But then people started to wave their hands! That was when I knew that they were getting into it!
Honami: Also, it sounded like some people were waiting to see us.
Ichika: That's right! It definitely felt like we were able to give those who enjoy our music a solid performance.
Shindo: That's wonderful to hear.
Shindo: And I'm sure those who hadn't heard of Leo/need prior to today now know what your music is about.
Honami: I certainly hope so...
Saki: Hehe... I hope we get to play at another big venue like this!
Shiho: Don't hope. We're gonna.
Shiho: Because we need to keep moving forward.
Honami: Hehe. You're absolutely right.
???: Great show, everyone.
Ichika: Oh...!
Shindo: Great show to all of you as well.
Mio: Thank you. Sorry, but we wanted to pop in and say hi.
Iori: You girls were awesome today.
Iori: Not only did it seem like you had more fun than usual, the crowd went totally nuts.
Saki: Iori...!
Saku: Yeah, it was a great show. Ours was the best, of course.
Shiho: Credit where credit's due, anemone was pretty awesome.
Ichika: She's right. I nearly got sucked into the vortex you created.
Saki: Me too! That song just grabbed my heart and never let go!
Saki: And then, when STANDOUT played...
Iori: Hehe.
Iori: Hey, if you're all free after this, why don't we throw an after-party together?
Shiho: An after-party?
Iori: You're still all wound up from the show, right?
Iori: Plus, we don't get to meet up like this very often. It'd be nice to have more time to talk about music.
Mio: Oh, then... How about that place? The one we always go to.
Iori: *Nod* That's the plan.
Saki: We get to throw an after-party at your usual hangout...?! Yes, please! I wanna go!
Ichika: Oh, but...
Shindo: It's okay.
Shindo: You passed with flying colors today, so please feel free to go and celebrate.
Honami: Thank you very much!
Shindo: However, these girls are still in high school, so please make sure they're allowed to go home before it gets too late.
Iori: Of course. We'll be careful.
Iori: Anyway, now that you've all received permission...
Iori: Shall we?
Saki: Yes!
Ichika: Can you tell us more about the place we're about to go to?
Iori: It's a cafe. It's small, but it's a place where true music lovers gather.
Mio: It's such a great place. They have a grand piano that people can play, everyone there loves talking about music...
Mio: We stop by pretty often after practices. We even throw most of our after-parties there.
Shiho: Oh, really...?
Saki: This is so exciting! I can't wait to see it!
Mio: Oh, there it is.
Iori: I hope it's open.
Saki: Wow...!
